<topic xml:id="openwebui-downloading-ai-models-from-ollama"
 role="task" xml:lang="en"
 xmlns="http://docbook.org/ns/docbook" version="5.2"
 xmlns:its="http://www.w3.org/2005/11/its"
 xmlns:xi="http://www.w3.org/2001/XInclude"
 xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink"
 xmlns:trans="http://docbook.org/ns/transclusion">
  <info>
    <title>Downloading AI models from &ollama;</title>
    <meta name="maintainer" content="tbazant@suse.com" its:translate="no"/>
    <abstract>
      <para>
        &ollama; (<link xlink:href="https://ollama.com/"/>) is an online
        repository that hosts open source AI models. This procedure describes
        how to download and use these models from the &owui; interface.
      </para>
    </abstract>
  </info>
  <procedure>
    <itemizedlist>
      <title>Requirements</title>
      <listitem>
        <xi:include href="../snippets/openwebui-requirement-admin-privileges.xml"/>
      </listitem>
    </itemizedlist>
    <step>
      <para>
        In the bottom left of the &owui; window, click your avatar icon to open
        the user menu and select <guimenu>Admin Panel</guimenu>.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Click the <guimenu>Settings</guimenu> tab and select
        <guimenu>Models</guimenu> from the left menu.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        In the top-right corner of the screen, click the small
        <quote>download</quote> icon to open the <guimenu>Manage
        Models</guimenu> screen.
      </para>
      <figure xml:id="fig-owui-dld-ollama-model">
        <title>Downloading &ollama; AI models</title>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject role="fo">
            <imagedata fileref="owui-dld-ollama-model.png" width="100%"/>
          </imageobject>
          <imageobject role="html">
            <imagedata fileref="owui-dld-ollama-model.png" width="100%"/>
          </imageobject>
          <textobject role="description"><phrase>Downloading &ollama; AI models</phrase>
          </textobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        On the <link xlink:href="https://ollama.com/library">&ollama; library
        page</link>, identify the model tag of an AI model that you want to
        download, for example, <literal>gemma3:4b</literal>.
      </para>
    </step>
    <step>
      <para>
        Paste the model tag in the <guimenu>Pull a model from
        Ollama.com</guimenu> input field and confirm by clicking the small
        download button on the right.
      </para>
      <figure xml:id="fig-owui-dld-model-tag">
        <title>Entering model tag to download</title>
        <mediaobject>
          <imageobject role="fo">
            <imagedata fileref="owui-dld-model-tag.png" width="75%"/>
          </imageobject>
          <imageobject role="html">
            <imagedata fileref="owui-dld-model-tag.png" width="75%"/>
          </imageobject>
          <textobject role="description"><phrase>Entering model tag to download</phrase>
          </textobject>
        </mediaobject>
      </figure>
      <para>
        The model download starts and, after it is finished, the model will be
        available as a base model for AI interaction.
      </para>
    </step>
  </procedure>
</topic>
